---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Programmatic Remnant Banner Inventory for Ad Networks | AdBunny"
  description="Access aggregated remnant banner inventory programmatically. AI-optimized placement, real-time performance data, no manual tuning required."
  keywords="programmatic banner inventory access, remnant inventory for advertisers, ad network demand partner, real-time bidding banner ads, media buying remnant inventory"
>
<section class="page-header">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Programmatic Access to Aggregated Remnant Banner Inventory</h1>
    <p>AdBunny gives ad networks, DSPs, and media buyers efficient access to remnant banner inventory across our publisher network — with AI-driven placement optimization and real-time performance reporting, instead of manual, publisher-by-publisher negotiation.</p>
    <div class="hero-actions" style="margin-top:2rem;justify-content:center;">
      <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">Talk to Our Demand Team</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="two-col">
      <div class="col-text">
        <span class="label">The Challenge</span>
        <h2>The Scale Problem With Remnant Inventory</h2>
        <p>Remnant inventory is valuable, but it's fragmented across thousands of individual publishers, each with different setups, fill patterns, and placement quality. Accessing it efficiently — and optimizing performance across it — doesn't scale with manual processes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-visual">
        <img src="/images/advertiser-marketplace.png" alt="Analogy: central marketplace trading desk connecting merchants and buyers — like AdBunny connects publishers and demand partners">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-alt">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="label">How We Solve It</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">How AdBunny Solves It</h2>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-icon"><Icon name="lucide:link" /></div>
        <h3>Aggregated access</h3>
        <p>Reach remnant banner inventory across the AdBunny publisher network through a single integration, instead of negotiating site by site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-icon"><Icon name="lucide:bar-chart-3" /></div>
        <h3>AI-optimized placement</h3>
        <p>AdBunny's optimization layer continuously improves banner performance across placements without requiring manual tuning on your end.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-icon"><Icon name="lucide:radio" /></div>
        <h3>Real-time reporting</h3>
        <p>Get placement-level performance data as it happens, so you can evaluate spend efficiency and adjust strategy with current information, not lagging reports.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="label">Who It's For</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">Who This Is For</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">Ad networks, DSPs, and media buyers looking to deploy banner campaigns efficiently against remnant inventory at scale, with data to back up performance decisions.</p>
    <div class="col-visual">
      <img src="/images/ai-post-office.png" alt="Analogy: smart routing system that optimizes every letter — like AdBunny optimizes every impression">
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-cta">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Get Efficient Access to Remnant Banner Demand</h2>
    <p>Talk to our team about integrating with the AdBunny network.</p>
    <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">Talk to Our Demand Team</a>
  </div>
</section>
</BaseLayout>
